8738/ Shake n' Vac jingle maker Jonathan Hodge, from Folkestone, dies aged 78]</ref>\n*[[Jeff Ingber]], 83, English table tennis player.<ref>[https://www.ittf.com/2019/07/15/jeff-inger-one-earliest-junior-internationals-passes-away/ Jeff Ingber, one the earliest junior internationals passes away]</ref>\n*[[Greg Johnson (ice hockey)|Greg Johnson]], 48, Canadian ice hockey player ([[Detroit Red Wings]], [[Nashville Predators]], [[Pittsburgh Penguins]]), Olympic silver medalist ([[Ice hockey at the 1994 Winter Olympics|1994]]), suicide by gunshot.<ref>[https://eu.usatoday.com/story/sports/nhl/2019/07/09/greg-johnson-nashville-predators-red-wings-penguins-blackhawks-dies-48/1683259001/ Greg Johnson, who played for Nashville Predators and three other NHL teams, dies at 48]</ref>\n*[[Wolfgang Joklik]], 92, Austrian-born American virologist.<ref>[https://www.legacy.com/obituaries/heraldsun/obituary.aspx?pid=193355619 Dr. Wolfgang Karl (Bill) Joklik]</ref>\n*[[Joe Kadenge]], 84, Kenyan football player ([[A.F.C. Leopards|Abaluhya]]) and manager ([[Kenya national football team|national team]]), complications from a stroke.<ref>[https://www.capitalfm.co.ke/news/2019/07/football-legend-joe-kadenge-is-dead/ Football legend Joe Kadenge is dead]</ref>\n*[[Elizabeth Killick]], 94, British naval electronics engineer, heart attack.<ref>[https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/elizabeth-killick-obituary-5j8t98mvl Dr Elizabeth Killick obituary]</ref>\n*[[Ekaterina Koroleva (handballer)|Ekaterina Koroleva]], 20, Russian handballer, drowned.<ref>[http://www.eurohandball.com/article/33017 Russian beach handball player dies after swimming accident]</ref>\n*[[Stefan Kwocza\u0142a]], 85, Polish speedway rider, [[Polish Individual Speedway Championship|national individual champion]] (1959).<ref>[https://sportowefakty.wp.pl/zuzel/831343/nie-zyje-legenda-czestochowskiego-zuzla-stefan-kwoczala-mial-85-lat Nie \u017cyje legenda cz\u0119stochowskiego \u017cu\u017cla. Stefan Kwocza\u0142a mia\u0142 85 l