{"title_page": "Islip High School", "text_new": "{{Infobox school\n| name = Islip High School\n| image =IHS-BIRDSEYE.jpg\n| imagesize =\n| logo =\n| caption =\n| location = 2508 Union Blvd<br />[[Islip, New York]]\n| country = [[United States]]\n| coordinates = {{Coord|40|43|50|N|73|13|13|W|type:edu_region:US-NY_source:GNIS-953842|display=inline,title}}\n| district = [[Islip School District]]\n| principal = Mr. LaRochester\n| faculty = 86.22 (on [[full-time equivalent|FTE]] basis)<ref name=NCES>{{Cite web |url=http://nces.ed.gov/ccd/schoolsearch/school_detail.asp?Search=1&SchoolID=361554001324&ID=361554001324 |title=Islip High School |publisher=[[National Center for Education Statistics]] |accessdate=18 December 2019 |quote=Total Students: 993 (2017\u20132018)}}</ref>\n| ratio = 11.52<ref name=NCES />\n| enrollment = 993 (2017-18)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nces.ed.gov/ccd/schoolsearch/school_detail.asp?Search=1&DistrictID=3615540&ID=361554001324|title=ISLIP HIGH SCHOOL|publisher=National Center for Education Statistics|accessdate=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| type = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]]\n| us_nces_school_id = 361554001324\n| grades = [[Education in the United States#School grades|9\u201312]]\n| conference =\n| motto =\n| mascot = Buccaneers\n| mascot image =\n| nickname = \n| colors = Purple and Gold \n| established = \n| homepage = [http://www.islipufsd.org/our_schools/high_school Islip High School]\n}}\n'''Islip High School''' is the public high school in [[Islip (hamlet), New York|Islip]], in Suffolk County, New York on the South Shore of Long Island. The principal is Mr. LaRochester and the assistant principals are Mr. Curtis Juengerkes and Ms. Lisa Ward. The complete lists of current and past graduates, Regents exam scores, and other important information can be found on the New York State School Information Report Comprehensive School Report, as well as on Newsday.com, as current as the 2010-2011 school year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Islip High School|url=http://www.NYSED.gov|publisher=New York State Education Department|accessdate=26 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Islip High School|url=http://www.Newsday.com|publisher=Newsday|accessdate=26 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Curriculum==\n\nThe curriculum at the Islip high School includes all academic areas, as well as art, music, and technology. Beginning at the Middle School level, honors classes are offered in English, social studies, mathematics, science, Italian, and Spanish. Advanced Placement courses are offered in, including but not limited to, Art History, English Language and Composition, English Literature and Composition, US History, European History, US Government and Politics, Human Geography, Calculus AB, Statistics, Biology, Chemistry, Physics 1 & 2, Environmental Science, Seminar, Research, and the Italian and Spanish Languages.<ref>{{cite web|title=Islip School District|url=http://www.islipufsd.org|publisher=Islip School District|accessdate=26 April 2012}}</ref> The High School also offers dual credit options through affiliations with Suffolk County Community College (Math & Music), Farmingdale State College (Business & Technology), Hofstra (Engineering), and St. John's University (Italian, Business, & Science).\n \nThe  school offers multiple music groups, including concert band, wind ensemble, marching band, jazz band, chamber orchestra, concert orchestra, chorus, music theory, and performing arts. Alongside the performing arts class musical production, there is also an annual musical production.\n\n==Musical Productions==\n* [[Little Shop of Horrors (musical)]] - 2020/2021 (performing arts class production)\n*[[Joseph and the Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat]] -2020\n*[[Mamma Mia! (musical)]] - 2019/2020 (performing arts class production)\n* [[Grease (musical)]] - 2019 \n* [[The Little Mermaid (musical)]] - 2018/2019 (performing arts class production)\n* [[Pippin (musical)]]- 2018 (performing arts class production)\n* [[Legally Blonde (musical)]]- 2018\n* The Wiz- 2017\n* [[Into the Woods]] - 2016/2017 (Performing Arts Class production)\n* [[The Sound of Music]] - 2016 (Performing Arts Class production)\n* [[Big Fish (musical)]] -2016\n* [[Catch Me If You Can (musical)]] - 2015 (Long Island Premier)\n* [[Footloose (musical)]] - 2014\n* [[Beauty and the Beast (musical)]] - 2013\n* [[Little Shop of Horrors (musical)]] - 2012\n\n==Notable alumni==\n*[[Peter Lemongello]], singer{{cn|date=July 2014}}\n*[[Tom Veryzer]], Major League Baseball player<ref>{{cite news|last1=Marcus|first1=Steven|title=Tom Veryzer dead, LIer had 12-year career in majors|url=http://www.newsday.com/sports/baseball/tom-veryzer-dead-lier-had-12-year-career-in-majors-1.8746348|accessdate=July 10, 2014|publisher=Newsday|date=July 9, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Chris Wade (fighter)]], UFC Fighter\n*[[Larry Saperstein]], actor\n\n==Awards==\nIn 2003, the cafeteria at Islip High School received the award for the Most Improved Cafeteria in the State from the New York State School  FoodService Association <ref>{{cite news|title=Islip Youth Wins Award|newspaper=County Review|date=2 July 1942}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Pereira|first=Mary E.|title=Islip High School Cafeteria Earns Recognition|newspaper=Newsday|date=26 Oct 2003}}</ref>\n\nIslip\u2019s performing arts students have also won Teeny Awards from the Islip Arts Counsel. Past winners include Nicholas D\u2019Auria (Supporting Actor in a musical, 2019) and Antonia Castronova (Best Cameo actress in a Musical [2018], Best Supporting Actress in a musical [2019])\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions with year of establishment missing]]\n[[Category:Islip (town), New York]]\n[[Category:Public high schools in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Schools in Suffolk County, New York]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox school\n| name = Islip High School\n| image =IHS-BIRDSEYE.jpg\n| imagesize =\n| logo =\n| caption =\n| location = 2508 Union Blvd<br />[[Islip, New York]]\n| country = [[United States]]\n| coordinates = {{Coord|40|43|50|N|73|13|13|W|type:edu_region:US-NY_source:GNIS-953842|display=inline,title}}\n| district = [[Islip School District]]\n| principal = Mr. LaRochester\n| faculty = 86.22 (on [[full-time equivalent|FTE]] basis)<ref name=NCES>{{Cite web |url=http://nces.ed.gov/ccd/schoolsearch/school_detail.asp?Search=1&SchoolID=361554001324&ID=361554001324 |title=Islip High School |publisher=[[National Center for Education Statistics]] |accessdate=18 December 2019 |quote=Total Students: 993 (2017\u20132018)}}</ref>\n| ratio = 11.52<ref name=NCES />\n| enrollment = 993 (2017-18)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nces.ed.gov/ccd/schoolsearch/school_detail.asp?Search=1&DistrictID=3615540&ID=361554001324|title=ISLIP HIGH SCHOOL|publisher=National Center for Education Statistics|accessdate=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| type = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]]\n| us_nces_school_id = 361554001324\n| grades = [[Education in the United States#School grades|9\u201312]]\n| conference =\n| motto =\n| mascot = Buccaneers\n| mascot image =\n| nickname = \n| colors = Purple and Gold \n| established = \n| homepage = [http://www.islipufsd.org/our_schools/high_school Islip High School]\n}}\n'''Islip High School''' is the public high school in [[Islip (hamlet), New York|Islip]], in Suffolk County, New York on the South Shore of Long Island. The principal is Mr. LaRochester and the assistant principals are Mr. Curtis Juengerkes and Ms. Lisa Ward. The complete lists of current and past graduates, Regents exam scores, and other important information can be found on the New York State School Information Report Comprehensive School Report, as well as on Newsday.com, as current as the 2010-2011 school year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Islip High School|url=http://www.NYSED.gov|publisher=New York State Education Department|accessdate=26 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Islip High School|url=http://www.Newsday.com|publisher=Newsday|accessdate=26 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Curriculum==\n\nThe curriculum at the Islip high School includes all academic areas, as well as art, music, and technology. Beginning at the Middle School level, honors classes are offered in English, social studies, mathematics, science, Italian, and Spanish. Advanced Placement courses are offered in, including but not limited to, Art History, English Language and Composition, English Literature and Composition, US History, European History, US Government and Politics, Human Geography, Calculus AB, Statistics, Biology, Chemistry, Physics 1 & 2, Environmental Science, Seminar, Research, and the Italian and Spanish Languages.<ref>{{cite web|title=Islip School District|url=http://www.islipufsd.org|publisher=Islip School District|accessdate=26 April 2012}}</ref> The High School also offers dual credit options through affiliations with Suffolk County Community College (Math & Music), Farmingdale State College (Business & Technology), Hofstra (Engineering), and St. John's University (Italian, Business, & Science).\n \nThe  school offers multiple music groups, including concert band, wind ensemble, marching band, jazz band, chamber orchestra, concert orchestra, chorus, music theory, and performing arts. Alongside the performing arts class musical production, there is also an annual musical production.\n\n==Musical Productions==\n*[[Joseph and the Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat]] -2020\n*[[Mamma Mia! (musical)]] - 2019/2020 (performing arts class production)\n* [[Grease (musical)]] - 2019 \n* [[The Little Mermaid (musical)]] - 2018/2019 (performing arts class production)\n* [[Pippin (musical)]]- 2018 (performing arts class production)\n* [[Legally Blonde (musical)]]- 2018\n* The Wiz- 2017\n* [[Into the Woods]] - 2016/2017 (Performing Arts Class production)\n* [[The Sound of Music]] - 2016 (Performing Arts Class production)\n* [[Big Fish (musical)]] -2016\n* [[Catch Me If You Can (musical)]] - 2015 (Long Island Premier)\n* [[Footloose (musical)]] - 2014\n* [[Beauty and the Beast (musical)]] - 2013\n* [[Little Shop of Horrors (musical)]] - 2012\n\n==Notable alumni==\n*[[Peter Lemongello]], singer{{cn|date=July 2014}}\n*[[Tom Veryzer]], Major League Baseball player<ref>{{cite news|last1=Marcus|first1=Steven|title=Tom Veryzer dead, LIer had 12-year career in majors|url=http://www.newsday.com/sports/baseball/tom-veryzer-dead-lier-had-12-year-career-in-majors-1.8746348|accessdate=July 10, 2014|publisher=Newsday|date=July 9, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Chris Wade (fighter)]], UFC Fighter\n*[[Larry Saperstein]], actor\n\n==Awards==\nIn 2003, the cafeteria at Islip High School received the award for the Most Improved Cafeteria in the State from the New York State School  FoodService Association <ref>{{cite news|title=Islip Youth Wins Award|newspaper=County Review|date=2 July 1942}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Pereira|first=Mary E.|title=Islip High School Cafeteria Earns Recognition|newspaper=Newsday|date=26 Oct 2003}}</ref>\n\nIslip\u2019s performing arts students have also won Teeny Awards from the Islip Arts Counsel. Past winners include Nicholas D\u2019Auria (Supporting Actor in a musical, 2019) and Antonia Castronova (Best Cameo actress in a Musical [2018], Best Supporting Actress in a musical [2019])\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions with year of establishment missing]]\n[[Category:Islip (town), New York]]\n[[Category:Public high schools in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Schools in Suffolk County, New York]]\n", "name_user": "Wikiwikiwhatnow", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMusical Productions", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islip_High_School"}
{"title_page": "Yagrysh", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Yagrysh\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u042f\u0433\u0440\u044b\u0448\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Vozhegodsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|60|22|N|39|09|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/vozhegodskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u0436\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Yagrysh''' ({{lang-ru|\u042f\u0433\u0440\u044b\u0448}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Beketovskoye Rural Settlement, [[Vozhegodsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 6 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Vozhega]] is 81 km, to Beketovskaya is 2 km. Nikulskaya, Kropufinskaya, Andreyevskaya are the nearest rural localities.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Vozhegodsky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vozhegodsky District]]\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n[[Category:Russian Rural Settlement]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Yagrysh\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u042f\u0433\u0440\u044b\u0448\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Vozhegodsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|60|22|N|39|09|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/vozhegodskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u0436\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Yagrysh''' ({{lang-ru|\u042f\u0433\u0440\u044b\u0448}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Beketovskoye Rural Settlement, [[Vozhegodsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 6 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Vozhega]] is 81 km, to Beketovskaya is 2 km. Nikulskaya, Kropufinskaya, Andreyevskaya are the nearest rural localities.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Vozhegodsky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vozhegodsky District]]\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Mgarland1", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added Category", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yagrysh"}
